#### 23.1 Automatically generated

The basic report layout is automatically generated when you change to the Reporting work
space. The layout you define in the analysis is automatically converted into the report template.

Figure 23.2 - ANALYSIS Layout converion to REPORTINGLayout

23.1.1 Generic Report structure

When the report is generated the following structure is automatically available to you.

â¶ Report cover sheet : The cover sheet is the first page of the report. You can edit this pages

with the tools discussed below.

â¶ Project Parameters : This page shows all project parameters of all loaded data files. This

can cover many pages when you load many data files which have plenty of parameters
stored inside.

â¶ Pages : The pages are automatically generated from the ANALYSIS work space. All pages

from the ANALYSIS are transferred to the report.

#### 23.3 Report Layout configuration

23.3.1 Introduction

Converting the layout of the analysis into a report is easy. However, if you like to build a cus-
tomized report which shows individual cover sheets, header or footer sections you need to
switch to the layout designer. With the layout designer you can define your own report template
(IRL) file which includes all individually defined settings. On many reports the following inform-
ation is included:

â¶ Time when report is created

â¶ Name of the data file

â¶ Start or stop of measurement

â¶ Information about the project parameters saved to the data file

â¶ Project parameters of the current IWF file

â¶ Statistic functions like min, max average of a channel displayed in a table

23.3.2 Layout designer

With the layout designer you can create your own report templates with your specific layout. The
difference to the drawing elements mentioned above is that the changes are saved in a seper-
ate IRL report file.

#### 23.5 Report font and line size for Yt and XY diagrams

You can increase on the report for Yt-, XY diagram the sickness of lines in the graph, legend
and axis. You need to update the Settings.XML file. The file is located in Program Data dir-
ectory.

**IPETRONIK IPEMOTION SOFTWARE - USER MANUAL | Â©IPETRONIK 2024. ALL RIGHTS RESERVED. | VERSION -2024-R2- | JULY 2024 985**


![Image](data:image/jpeg;base64,)


![Image](data:image/jpeg;base64,)


---

â¶ C:\ProgramData\IPETRONIK\IPEmotion 2024 R2

The new entry in the file should be:

<ReportingSettings>

<ReportingVisualOffset>4</ReportingVisualOffset>

</ReportingSettings>

Figure 23.31 - Reporting settings

Close IPEmotion before you modify the Setting.XML file . If you edit the file and close IPEmotion
afterwards your changes will not be saved and overwritten by the IPEmotion settings. The
Visual Offset should be in the Range:

â¶ 0 = default

â¶ 4 = larger

â¶ 10 = large

â¶ Not recommended: You can add also very large numbers. There is no control in the Set-

tings.XML.
